    "body": "Closing this issue. After further work, I've discovered that `relayXDomainMessages` does some nice error handling that \r\n\r\n```\r\n let status: MessageStatus \r\n while (status !== MessageStatus.READY_FOR_RELAY) { \r\n   status = await env.messenger.getMessageStatus(transaction) \r\n   await sleep(1000) \r\n } \r\n  \r\n await env.messenger.finalizeMessage(transaction) \r\n```\r\n\r\ndoes not do. As a result, I'm actually going to go backwards and prefer that the integration tests use `relayXDomainMessages` everywhere for consistency.",
